Now, ground your arms.

22
00:03:10,093 --> 00:03:11,845
Take three paces back...

23
00:03:12,013 --> 00:03:13,207
...slowly.

24
00:03:15,933 --> 00:03:18,572
Move three paces back, now!

25
00:03:20,173 --> 00:03:22,892
The game's over, Harry. We lost again.

26
00:03:26,493 --> 00:03:28,165
Quick...march!

27
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,532
Pick your feet up!

28
00:03:42,093 --> 00:03:44,004
Move it, you Fenian bastard!

29
00:03:56,893 --> 00:03:58,485
Open the gates!

30
00:04:08,493 --> 00:04:11,053
Show me the ringleaders
of this little farce.

31
00:04:16,253 --> 00:04:17,606
Pearse...

32
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,925
...with the gunner eye.

33
00:04:22,173 --> 00:04:23,288
McDonagh.

34
00:04:27,293 --> 00:04:28,806
Thomas Clarke.

35
00:04:33,853 --> 00:04:35,127
Connolly.

36
00:04:36,253 --> 00:04:37,925
Get up, you Fenian swine.

37
00:04:38,013 --> 00:04:40,322
Wait, Michael. Wait.

38
00:04:40,493 --> 00:04:41,528
Till when?

39
00:04:41,693 --> 00:04:43,251
Till the next time.

40
00:04:52,813 --> 00:04:54,246
Eamon de Valera.

41
00:05:03,693 --> 00:05:05,285
What happens next time?

42
00:05:05,453 --> 00:05:08,729
We won't play by their rules.
We'll invent our own.

43
00:05:08,893 --> 00:05:09,848
Fire!

44
00:05:13,453 --> 00:05:14,886
'The fact...

45
00:05:16,253 --> 00:05:18,164
'...that l was born in...

46
